						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/Commodities/Fisheries/Related-developments/New-study-shows-probiotics-help-fish-grow-up-faster-and-healthier" title="New study shows probiotics help fish grow up faster and healthier " alt="link">New study shows probiotics help fish grow up faster and healthier </a></h2>

	
					<p>Probiotics like those found in yogurt are not only good for people – they are also good for fish. A new study by scientists at the Institute of Marine and Environmental Technology (Baltimore, USA) found that feeding probiotics to baby zebrafish accelerated their development and increased their chances of survival into adulthood. This research could help increase the success of raising rare ornamental fish to adulthood. It also has implications for aquaculture, since accelerating the development of fish larvae – the toughest time for survival ­– could mean a more efficient and safe system for bringing fish to the dinner table.<a href="http://www.umces.edu/imet/release/2012/dec/03/new-study-shows-probiotics-help-fish-grow-faster-and-healthier" target="_self">http://www.umces.edu/imet/release/2012/dec/03/new-study-shows-probiotics-help-fish-grow-faster-and-healthier</a>&nbsp;(IMET, 3/12/2012)&nbsp;</p>
							<p><span class="date">22/05/2013</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/Commodities/Fisheries/Related-developments/New-study-shows-probiotics-help-fish-grow-up-faster-and-healthier">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
